# Running Tests

This project uses a `venv/` virtual environment. Always use the venv Python to run tests:

```powershell
# Correct — run pytest via venv Python (no activation needed)
C:\Repos\db-inspector-mcp\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pytest tests/ -v

# Run a specific test file
C:\Repos\db-inspector-mcp\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pytest tests/test_config.py -v
```

Do NOT run bare `python -m pytest` or `pytest` — the system Python does not have project dependencies installed.

Do NOT run `pip install` to fix missing dependencies — the venv already has everything installed.

# Shell Environment

This project runs on Windows with PowerShell. Avoid bash-only commands:
- Use `Select-Object -First N` instead of `head -N`
- Use `Select-Object -Last N` instead of `tail -N`
- Use `Select-String` instead of `grep` (or use `rg` which is available)
